# used from custom_init_and_run
def add_release(model, index):
    
    if index in release_times_nonperiodic:
        release_time = release_times_nonperiodic[index]
    else:
        release_time = 0.0000005 * index
    
    rs = m.ReleaseSite(
        name = "release_site_" + str(index),
        complex = m.Complex("ACh"),
        location = release_location,
        release_time = release_time,
        number_to_release = numbers_to_release[index - 1]
    )
    model.add_release_site(rs)


def custom_init_and_run(model):
    # When uncommented, this function is called after all the model
    # components defined in CellBlender were added to the model.
    # It allows to add additional model components before initialization 
    # is done and then to customize how simulation is ran.
    
    # add releases 
    for i in range(1, 304):
        add_release(model, i)
    
    model.initialize()
    model.run_iterations(parameters.ITERATIONS)
    model.end_simulation()
